Package: eathquakeGeoms
Type: Package
Title: Eathquake Data Cleaning And Graphics Display
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Rony Sulca (ronybsulca@berkeley.edu)
Maintainer: Rony Sulca <ronybsulca@berkeley.edu>
Description: eathquakeGeoms includes a variety of functions to help clean and display the 
    eathquakes in the NOAA data frame (National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration).
      To clean the dataset, use 'eq_loaction_clean' and 'eq_clean_data'. To analyze the data,
    use the new geom 'GeomTimeline', through its calling function 'geom_timeline'. To see the location
    of the earquakes through properly annotated circles in a leaflet map, use 'eq_map' and 'eq_create_label'.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports: leaflet,
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    scales,
    stringr
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
